This is a simple Python-based calculator program that performs basic arithmetic operations:

Addition (+)

Subtraction (-)

Multiplication (*)

Division (/)

The program asks the user to input two numbers and a mathematical operator, then displays the result.

ðŸ’» How It Works
The user is prompted to enter:

The first number

The second number

The operation they want to perform (+, -, *, /)

The program performs the operation and prints the result in the format:
num1 operator num2 = result
